{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F1","question":"Q5","summary":"Use warn-only first for new quality gates; T3 can skip warn-only because it is comment guidance plus scaffold validation.","sources":[".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/save-quality-gate.ts:226-258",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/validation/save-quality-gate.ts:753-848",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/save-quality-gate.vitest.ts:182-215",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-save.ts:2130-2213",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:93-125"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F2","question":"Q5","summary":"WARNING is not safely advisory under completion because --strict promotes warnings to validation failure; T4 should start INFO or behind explicit strict-safe rollout controls.","sources":[".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:27-35",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh:930-945",".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh:1056-1059",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:147-160",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/research/iterations/iteration-002.md:14-16"]}
