{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F4","question":"Q5","summary":"T3 -> T4 -> T2 -> T1 is risk-based rather than dependency-based; the three planned phases are technically independent and T1 remains deferred.","sources":[".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/spec.md:64-68",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/spec.md:128-133",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/peck-teachings-analysis.md:289-301"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F5","question":"Q5","summary":"Verdict ownership should scale with blast radius: self-attestation plus validation is adequate for T3/T4/T2, but T1 coverage should use a separate read-only reviewer or deep-review-like verdict.","sources":[".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:121-125",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:120-130",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/004-constitutional-rule-review/spec.md:118-148",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/peck-teachings-analysis.md:67-77",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:29-33"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F6","question":"Q5","summary":"Per-phase failure modes are distinct: T3 TEMPLATE_HEADERS regressions, T4 false positives/strict escalation, T2 scope creep into expiry/deletion, and T1 false confidence from weak tests.","sources":[".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:65-68",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/research/iterations/iteration-001.md:17-49",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:147-160",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/004-constitutional-rule-review/spec.md:97-100",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:15-33"]}
{"type":"finding","iteration":5,"id":"Q5-F7","question":"Q5","summary":"Rollout success metrics should be phase-specific: scaffold + strict validation for T3, warning volume/no new errors for T4, read-only dynamic enumeration for T2, and computable AC traceability for future T1.","sources":[".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/002-self-check-templates/spec.md:136-141",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:127-140",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/004-constitutional-rule-review/spec.md:118-128",".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-peck-teachings-adoption/001-peck-teachings-for-spec-kit/research/iterations/iteration-004.md:35-44"]}
